:FED.
4. Credit assessment
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
4.1. Information for credit assessment
:SKRSLUT.
.br
For the purposes of performing a credit assessment on card account
applicants, &BANKNAVN. is entitled to demand the information that
&BANKNAVN. ordinarily uses for credit assessments, including pay
slips, tax returns, annual statements from SKAT (the Danish Tax
Authorities) and financial statements. In addition, &BANKNAVN. may
contact credit information agencies.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
A credit assessment may be performed at any time during the account
relationship. At the time of application and subsequently during the
account relationship, a credit assessment may be performed that
includes the card account holder's other positions with &BANKNAVN.. If
you decline to provide &BANKNAVN. with the information requested, this
will be considered material breach of contract - see Article 2.17 - and
all cards associated with the card account may be blocked without notice.
.br
Information about the blocking of cards will be communicated to the
account holder no later than simultaneously with the blocking of the cards.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
4.2. Rejection of an application
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The bank reserves the right to reject applications for cards. The bank
will normally decline to issue cards to persons who are listed in the
Experian Information Solutions register (formerly called RKI - Ribers
Kreditinformation).
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
